        <div class="section">
            <h3 class="section-title">10. Comments and Public Posts; Sharing on Third party Websites</h3>
            <p class="section-text">Arslin encourages active participation by users, including through user-generated comments or content on Arslin. However, please be aware that if you voluntarily disclose Information, personal or otherwise, on Arslin, that Information can be viewed, collected and used by others, including other users, search engines, advertisers, third party applications developers, and anyone with access to Arslin. Arslin has no control over the use, collection or disclosure of any Information that you post publicly on Arslin.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="section">
            <h3 class="section-title">11. Change of Control</h3>
            <p class="section-text">If Arslin, or substantially all of its assets, is acquired by another company or party, user Information will be one of the assets transferred or acquired by the purchaser. You acknowledge that such transfers may occur, and that any purchaser of Arslin or its assets may continue to collect, use and disclose your Information as set forth in this Policy.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="section">
            <h3 class="section-title">12. Security and Protection of Personally Identifying Information</h3>
            <p class="section-text">We have implemented reasonable security measures and practices in an effort to protect the confidentiality of your Personally Identifying Information (other than Personally Identifying Information that you have elected to disclose to others). However, no security system is impenetrable. It may be possible for third parties to intercept or access information you provide to Arslin. Arslin cannot guarantee the security of your Personally Identifying Information, nor can we guarantee that information you supply will not be intercepted while being transmitted to Arslin. It is important for you to protect against unauthorized access to your password(s) and computer or device, and to log off when using any shared computer.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="section">
            <h3 class="section-title">13. Children's Privacy</h3>
            <p class="section-text">Arslin does not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13 years of age.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="section">
            <h3 class="section-title">14. Changes to the Privacy Policy</h3>
            <p class="section-text">Arslin retains the discretion to amend or modify this Privacy Policy from time to time. Use and disclosure of Information we obtain is subject to the later of: (1) the Privacy Policy in effect at the time such Information is collected or (2) any subsequent Privacy Policy of which you have notice. If we make material changes to the way we collect, use or disclose Personally Identifying Information, we will notify you by posting a clear and prominent announcement on Arslin or through a direct communication. Your continued access to or use of Arslin following notice of material changes to this Privacy Policy shall constitute consent to any amendments and/or modifications. Your use of Arslin is entirely voluntary, and you may discontinue use of Arslin at any time.</p>
        </div>
        
